06/12/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Soldiers have killed a total of 14 Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) militants -- including several women -- in clashes along the Iraqi border since Tuesday, the Turkish military announced on Wednesday (December 5th). 
One Turkish soldier has been killed. 
According to a statement on the General Staff's website, troops have seized a large amount of weapons and documents.
Separately Wednesday, Turkish Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul suggested that roughly 70% of the PKK rebels are based in northern Iraq. 
He noted that despite international arrest warrants for PKK leaders, they continue to function unrestricted there. 
(Sabah, AFP, Iran TV, Reuters, DPA, Xinhua, Anadolu news agency - 05/12/07)
